{"id": "EUVD-2021-14851", "enisaUuid": "ad79f972-4c1d-3a03-9382-076f93f5aed7", "description": "An issue was discovered in GNOME GLib before 2.66.8. When g_file_replace() is used with G_FILE_CREATE_REPLACE_DESTINATION to replace a path that is a dangling symlink, it incorrectly also creates the target of the symlink as an empty file, which could conceivably have security relevance if the symlink is attacker-controlled. (If the path is a symlink to a file that already exists, then the contents of that file correctly remain unchanged.)", "datePublished": "2021-03-11T21:04:15", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-03T21:40:12", "baseScore": 5.3, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2021-28153.html", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2021:4385", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2021-28153", "https://advisories.mageia.org/CVE-2021-28153.html", "https://security.archlinux.org/CVE-2021-28153", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2021-28153.html", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:8418", "https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib/-/issues/2325", "https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce%40lists.fedoraproject.org/message/6RXTD5HCP2K4AAUSWWZTBKQNHRCTAEOF/", "https://security.netapp.com/advisory/ntap-20210416-0003/", "https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce%40lists.fedoraproject.org/message/ICUTQPHZNZWX2DZR46QFLQZRHVMHIILJ/", "https://security.gentoo.org/glsa/202107-13", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2022/06/msg00006.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2021-28153"], "assigner": "mitre", "epss": 0.53, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "076cbad8-438a-3c73-b9e9-45b04a7aec90", "product": {"name": "n/a"}, "product_version": "n/a"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "8dd521c1-0be4-37f1-8034-1e133accd52e", "vendor": {"name": "n/a"}}], "isExploited": false}